Static Residential IPs

If you are tired of being blocked by websites, want to mask your real IP, and looking to browse the net with low to noninterference, then static residential proxies are the thing for you. The combination of a strong and stable connection with a legit residential IP will give your business an edge over the competition.


What are Static IPs?

Internet protocol (IP) addresses are the unique code that is assigned to each computer when it connects to the Internet. The IP address is used to locate the computer and enables it to communicate with other connected computers.
The two main types of IP addresses are static when a computer has a single manually configured IP address, and dynamic, when each time the computer connects to the net it is assigned a new IP address by a DHCP server. A static IP address is normally assigned by an Internet Service Provider (ISP).
There are no perfect IP address solutions, and it is important to consider your needs and goals before choosing the right type for your business. Sometimes, it is better to use a static proxy, while other circumstances call for a dynamic IP address solution.


Advantages of a Static Residential IP

Static IP addresses do have two major advantages.

First, it is stable. Static IP addresses are more stable than dynamic IPs. since they don`t change, static connections avoid the constant interruption to the user`s connection dynamic IPs often cause. A static IP address does not change and will stay the same no matter what the user does. This feature makes it perfect for Businesses, looking to use a single static IP address to ease communications within a closed network or improve their data scraping operations.

Second, it is simple. Since they are configured just once, Static IP addresses are simpler to get and maintain. Static IP addresses are a lot easier to set up and manage with Domain Name System (DNS) servers, and if you are hosting servers of any type it is easier to find via DNS.
